<p><b>Hermann Hesse</b> (pronounced <span title="Pronunciation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA" title="Wikipedia:IPA">[ˈhɛʀman ˈhɛsə]</a></span>) (2 July 1877 – 9 August 1962) was a <a href="/wiki/Germany" title="Germany">German</a>-<a href="/wiki/Switzerland" title="Switzerland">Swiss</a> poet, novelist, and painter. In 1946, he received the <a href="/wiki/Nobel_Prize_in_Literature" title="Nobel Prize in Literature">Nobel Prize in Literature</a>. His best-known works include <i><a href="/wiki/Steppenwolf_(novel)" title="Steppenwolf (novel)">Steppenwolf</a></i>, <i><a href="/wiki/Siddhartha_(novel)" title="Siddhartha (novel)">Siddhartha</a></i>, and <i><a href="/wiki/The_Glass_Bead_Game" title="The Glass Bead Game">The Glass Bead Game</a></i> (also known as <i>Magister Ludi</i>) which explore an individual's search for authenticity, self-knowledge and spirituality.</p>
